In this presidential memorandum, President Barack Obama delegates authority to the Secretary of State regarding the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961. Specifically, the Secretary of State is given the authority to direct the drawdown of up to $15 million in nonlethal commodities and services from any department or agency of the United States to provide assistance for the Syrian Opposition Coalition (SOC) and the Supreme Military Council (SMC). Additionally, the Secretary of State is authorized to determine whether it is important to the security interests of the United States to provide such assistance to the SOC and the SMC, without regard to any other provision of law. The memorandum also instructs the Secretary of State to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.